     * [121]Ash
       It's good that you feel it in you butt because it probably means
       your technique is good (ie. knees behind toes, heels on floor
       etc.). The further you stick your butt out, the more you will work
       your butt and it also trains your body to be glute dominant which
       is good for injury prevention and triple extension of the lower
       limb. The action of the butt is to extend and flex the hip which is
       what's involved in squats, step ups etc so that's why you can feel
       it being worked.
       I suggest that you ditch the smith machine when doing squats. This
       will make your other leg muscles work harder to stabilise you.
       Also, where you position the weight effects which muscles are
       targeted. If you are doing back squats, the weight is further back
       which targets the back of your legs. If you do front squats, the
       weight is further forward which targets the front of your legs
       more. Front squats also help you to keep your balance and may a
       good option if you choose to ditch the smith machine.
       [122]Ash ¬∑ 8 years ago
