     * [123]Sweet Thang
       Personally if i used to squat it would be proper squats.
       I never use the smith machine. I presume that you are training on
       your own as you are you the smith machine.
       If you are doing squats you only go down to a 90 degree angle, you
       dont need to go lower than this.
       If you have just started squating it is normal to get some gluteus
       maximus discomfort, however your legs should be also feeling the
       same. With your leg work out, start by doing leg extensions to warm
       the legs up initially, then do your squats. If you widen your
       stance you will build up your inner thighs, if you narrow your
       stance you will build up your outer thighs. If you google Tom Platz
       you will see how immense thighs can look.
       Source(s): I've trained with the best
       [124]Sweet Thang ¬∑ 8 years ago
